  <summary date="2017-11-08T05:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Fallen Warrior Battlefield Cross Memorial Act

This bill states that the Department of Veterans Affairs may not prohibit the display of a Battlefield Cross in any national cemetery.

"Battlefield Cross" means a memorial monument in honor of fallen members of the Armed Forces that may include a replica of an inverted rifle, boots, helmets, and identification tag.</summary>
